properties.media:imagetext:
spirit airbus A319
airlines
Rev. Four
2/10/11
safety information
Federal regulations require compliance with crew instructions, lighted passenger
information signs and posted placards at all times. If you are seated at an exit and are
unable to understand the information on this card, please contact a flight attendant.
informacion de seguridad
Regulaciones federales requieren seguir las instruciones de la tripulación, y avisos de
no fumar y abrocharse el cinturón cuando esten iluminados. Si usted está sentado(a)
al lado de una salida de emergencia y no entiende la información contenida en esta
tarjeta, o no comprende y habla el idioma ingles, informe a un asistente de vuelo.
EXIT SEATS
Please notify a crewmember if you do not meet the following
criteria or do not wish to assist in an emergency. If you are seated
in an exit seat, you may be asked to assist the crew in an emergency
by performing the following functions:
• Follow oral instructions and hand signals given by the crew;
• Locate the emergency exit and determine if it is safe to open;
• Open the emergency exit as shown and secure the exit so it does
not impede use of the exit;
• Activate the slide, if provided, pass quickly through the emergency
exit, and assist others after exiting the aircraft;
• Select and follow a safe path away from the emergency exit.
No passenger may be seated in an exit seat if it is likely that
he/she is unable to perform any of the functions listed
above because:
• The person has insufficient mobility, strength, or dexterity in their
arms, hands, or legs;
• The person cannot see or hear well enough to perform the
functions illustrated on this card;
• The person cannot verbally relate information to other passengers
or lacks the ability to understand oral crew commands given by
crewmembers in English;
• The person is less than 15 years of age;
• The person has a condition or responsibilities, such as caring for
small children, that might prevent him/her from performing the
functions illustrated on this card;
• The person has a condition that might cause him/her harm if he/she
were to perform the functions illustrated on this card
Please do not remove this card from the airplane.
Por favor, no se lleve esta tarjeta del avión.
FINAL ASSEMBLY OF THIS AIRPLANE WAS COMPLETED IN GERMANY.
millsfield:images_texts:
Life Rafts Baisas Salvavidas
OPEN
ABRIR
If water level is above the sill of an exit, DO NOT OPEN! Redirect passengers to other exits.
Si el nivel de agua está sobre el borde de una salida, NO ABRIR! Redirija a los pasajeros a otras salidas
** Survival kits are located in galley compartments.
Equipos de Emergencia estan localizados en los compartimientos de la galera.
